# {{ project_name }} — environment variables (example / manifest).
#
# Copy to `.env`, fill in real values, then run `make verify-env` to check that
# nothing required is left unset or a placeholder:
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#   make verify-env
#
# Convention: a variable whose value below is __REPLACE_ME__ (or whose line is
# tagged `# required`) is REQUIRED — verify-env fails until you set it in `.env`.
# Variables with a real default value here are OPTIONAL. `.env` is gitignored;
# this file is committed and is the single source of truth for what the app reads
# from the environment.

# ── Examples — uncomment and adapt for your project ──────────────────────────
# A required secret you must provide before the app boots:
# API_TOKEN=__REPLACE_ME__

# A required value, tagged explicitly (works even if it has a sample value):
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@host:5432/db   # required

# An optional override with a sensible default (left as-is, verify-env ignores it):
# LOG_LEVEL=info
